        <h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
        <div class="content stack gap-4">
          <p>
            Since a young age, my passion for technology has been unwavering. My parents wished
            for me to pursue a career in medicine, and not wanting to disappoint them, I tried to
            follow-through. Despite this, I've always been fascinated with the latest advancements
            in computers and information technology. While studying life sciences at school, I
            eagerly enrolled in computer programming courses whenever possible. And outside of school,
            I spent my free time writing small programs, building computers, and tinkering with servers.
            In 2017, I finally decided to pursue my passion and started my journey in the IT industry by
            obtaining a diploma from Seneca College.
          </p>
          <p>
            For me, the power and versatility of technology is what makes this field so exciting.
            Being able to create tools and solutions that can make people's lives easier or more
            efficient is incredibly satisfying. I still remember the first project I took on as a
            professional, where I worked with a small company to develop a tool to speed up their
            turnaround time. This help them expand their business online and attract
            clients from all across Canada.
          </p>
          <p>
            One of the things I love about technology is that it's constantly evolving, with new tools,
            frameworks, and technologies being released every day. As a developer, I'm always eager
            to learn about these advancements and think about how they can be used to improve my projects
            and enhance my skills. Keeping up with the rapid pace of change can be challenging, but it's
            also part of what makes this field so exciting.
          </p>
          <p>
            When I'm not working, you can usually find me tinkering with servers. I have my own personal
            homelab project where I experiment with various tools such as Ansible, Docker, Kubernetes,
            Proxmox, and different storage solutions like MergerFS, SnapRAID, Unraid, and TrueNAS. One of
            the best things about my homelab is that it allows me to learn new skills while also having fun.
          </p>
          <p>
            Another passion of mine is climbing. Since a friend introduced me to indoor climbing in 2018,
            I've been hooked. I love the mental and physical challenges that climbing presents, and the
            feeling of accomplishment when I complete a difficult climb is truly exhilarating.
          </p>

